DESCRIPTION:IU Auditorium\, Union Board\, and IU Student Foundation are pr
 oud to present Magdalena Bay as they bring their kaleidoscopic pop univer
 se to the IU Auditorium stage on April 22 for this year's Little 500 conc
 ert.\nThe Los Angeles–based duo of Mica Tenenbaum and Matthew Lewin is kn
 own for infectious hooks\, synth-heavy beats\, and a wildly immersive pop
  sound that’s made them a must-see live act. Make plans to join in for a 
 night of futuristic pop\, high-energy visuals\, and songs that get stuck 
 in your head immediately to celebrate Little 500 week!\nLook out in your 
 email for a special code to get your student tickets on Feb 11.  Tickets 
 will open to the general public on Friday\, February 13.\nVisit here for 
 more information.\nAll Indiana University events\, groups\, activities\, 
 and educational\, cultural\, and historical observances welcome all IU st
 udents and other members of the Indiana University community.\n\nHosted b
 y: Indiana Memorial Union Board\, Indiana University Student Foundation\n
