DESCRIPTION:Advoates for Science at IU will host monthly in-person meeting
 s for all undergraduate and graduate student members. During these meetin
 gs\, we will facilitate discussions about current club events\, updates\,
  and opportunities. Additionally\, beyond these discussions\, the respect
 ive committees within ASIU (political action\, media outreach\, event pla
 nning\, and written journalism) will meet in order to collaborate on orga
 nization action items and plan for future initiatives. This meeting is go
 ing to be a necessary and consistent opportunity for all student members 
 of ASIU to meet in person\, discuss the most pressing environmental and s
 cientific policy issues at the time\, and work together on building new i
 deas for both personal development and broader action. In other words\, t
 his meeting will be a forum for discussion and progressive planning withi
 n ASIU that will maintain a spirit of community between members and foste
 r a motivated atmosphere of determination in physically and mentally acti
 ng for change.\n\nHosted by: Advocates for Science at IU\n\nAdditional In
 formation can be found at: https://beinvolved.indiana.edu/event/12066440
DTEND:20260428T010000Z
