CATEGORIES:Cultural
CATEGORIES:Arts & Humanities
DESCRIPTION:It’s About Time! -- It is always timely to talk about time\, b
 ut\, perhaps now more than ever\, time is of the essence. So\, what are w
 e waiting for?\nThe central theme of this conference is temporality – whi
 ch may be broadly defined as the study of time and experiences related to
  time. This includes individual and collective perceptions of the flow of
  time\; human and/or non-human experiences of time\; changes\, or perceiv
 ed changes in the flow of time and their effects on the pace and movement
  of life\, work\, and art.\n\nHosted by: Student Advisory Board of the De
 partment of Comparative Literature\n\nAdditional Information can be found
  at: https://beinvolved.indiana.edu/event/12327213
DTEND:20260501T210000Z
DTSTAMP:20260422T023824Z
DTSTART:20260501T130000Z
LOCATION:IMU Oak Room
